<br>
Examples of such changes would be:<br>
<br>
 -All Albion weapon specs should provide an anytime style that is comparable to Amethyst Slash.  For example:<br>
<br>
In Thrust, swap Wyvernfang with Liontooth in the style listing (so that you get Wyvernfang at 34 spec points) and change Wyvernfang so that it is an anytime style (removing it from the Tranquilize chain that no one uses) with a high bonus to hit, medium damage, medium fatigue, and a low defensive bonus.<br>
<br>
In Crush, swap Divine Hammer with Bone Crusher in the style listing (so that you get Divine Hammer at 39 spec points) and change Divine Hammer so that it is an anytime style (leave Back Crush as the only Crush rear positional) with a medium bonus to hit, high damage, and high fatigue.<br>
<br>
 -All level 50 styles should exhibit strong utility and should not be limited to a single class.  For example:<br>
<br>
In Crush, add a 10 second stun to Devastate.<br>
<br>
In Thrust, change Dragonfang entirely (removing the stun effect as well) to chain off of Wyvernfang (now an anytime style, as shown above) and have a high bonus to hit, high damage, high fatigue, and a long hinder.  Change Basiliskfang to require an evade and have a high bonus to hit, medium damage, low fatigue, a low penalty to defense, and a 7 second stun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=siryakk>Sir Yakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#000000>(5/2/03 2:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=129.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My 2 cents</span><hr size=1> Hotkeyable, toggleable, style stacks.<br>
<br>
One hotkey button that sets up an entire stack of styles.  When you swing, the highest style in the stack that is valid is used.<br>
<br>
When you toggle on a style stack, it stays active until you select a different style stack, or you toggle it off.<br>
<br>
This is like the current backup style system, but generalized, and made into less of a clickfest.  You pre arrange a list of styles to try, and use the best one (the top one) when you swing.<br>
<br>
Changing between style stacks makes sense when you change your tactical situation or goals.  But, reactionary and positional styles would happen naturally, instead of just (not) taking up space on your hotbars.<br>
<br>
Random implementation blather:<br>
A limit to the number of styles, possibly level based, might be reasonable.  No limit would also work.<br>
<br>
Lets say you had a style stack like this (all albion crush):<br>
Devastate (chains off Side Crush)<br>
Body Masher (chains off skull breaker)<br>
Side Crush (side positional)<br>
Skull Breaker (block reactionary)<br>
Bone Crusher (parry reactionary)<br>
Back Crush (back positional stun)<br>
Concussion (anytime)<br>
<br>
If you ran up to someone's face, and swung, you'd do a concussion.  If you where beside them, you'd try a side crush, which would chain on the next swing into a devastate if it connected.<br>
<br>
It makes reactionary and positional styles easier to use, and makes them count for more.  It also gives melee characters something to think about and talk about.<br>
